result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Attorney Leah Selmek appeared.  James T. Sempf appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Matter called. Appearances made. Matter was scheduled for plea and sentencing on all files - 21CF399, 22CM23, and 21CM389 Defendant does not appear due to quarantine status so plea and sentencing to be reset. Quarantine will be over by the weekend. Court resets plea and sentencing on all files. Court in recess.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for January 31, 2022 at 01:15 pm.

Defendant Kenneth D Behnke in court with attorney Leah Selmek.  James T. Sempf appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Asking for Plea and sentencing tomorrow.  Minutes filed.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for January 26, 2022 at 01:15 pm.
Signed bond filed with the court.
Scheduling Order will be provided to Attys via e-filing by the Court

TOTAL BOND COVERS 22CM23, 21CM389, 21CF399
Defendant shall not possess or consume alcohol.  Defendant shall not possess or use illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia.  Defendant will not possess any firearms, ammunition or other weapons.  Defendant will not in any way contact or attempt to contact any victim(s) listed and will avoid their residence/place of employment or any place they are located and will avoid causing any other person, other than defendant's attorney, from doing so on defendant's behalf.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as through the mail, by telephone, by way of electronic device, in person, or through a third party.  VICTIM(S)/RESIDENCE(S):  NO CONTACT WITH B.N.S. OR RESIDENCE.    Defendant shall personally ensure that payments are made under any Order for Income Withholding if the Court appoints an attorney for the defendant.
